                        <interp inst="t18430508-name-704" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN CROWSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of John Crowson, of Hungerford-street, Commercial-road. The prisoner lived servant with a lodger of mine at Christ<lb></lb>mas last, and I took her as a lodger afterwards—she was to pay 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a-week for lodging and board—she worked at slop-work in the day, and went out in the evening, but I do not know where—she quitted my house rather ab<lb></lb>ruptly, and I missed two pictures, a gown, and a shilling—I found the pic<lb></lb>tures at Raphael's, and the gown was at an eating-house—they are mine.</p>
               <p>
